<p class="setprojectup"><strong><em>Investing in demand-driven qualifications</em></strong></p>

<p>SKILLS was engaged by the Technical Education &amp; Vocational Training Authority (TEVTA) of Punjab to introduce demand-driven courses in their institutions. This was done by introducing the globally recognised City &amp; Guilds International Vocational Qualification (IVQ) programs in 50 TEVTA centres. The training in all the centres were standardized through Teaching Learning Resources (TLRs) developed by SKILLS. Further, a total of 300 permanent trainers were trained to deliver the City and Guilds IVQ Programs which the Punjab TEVTA implemented as a feelevying program scheme parallel to their regular TEVTA Courses. It has proven to be a success with enrolments exceeding 1000 learners.</p>

<p>The quality of training is reflected in the number of distinction passes earned by students, with one receiving the City &amp; Guilds Medal of Excellence. Graduates of the City &amp; Guilds programmes have found employment in reputed firms in Pakistan and overseas. SKILLS is currently working on linking other TEVTA programmes to these employment channels, adding further value.</p>

