<p class="setprojectup"><strong><em>Turnkey solutions for private sector vocational training (Since 2010)</em></strong></p>

<p>SKILLS provided Amantech &ndash; a subsidiary of the philanthropic Aman Foundation &ndash; with a turnkey solution for a technical and vocational training institute in Pakistan to cater to5000 students. The solution included equipment layout plans, advice on procuring equipment and recruitment of teaching staff, Training of Trainers (TOT), training supervision, training on centre management and the production of TLR material. The programmes are geared to producing graduates who can meet the needs of the private sector in Pakistan and overseas. In the first two phases the following programmes were offered: construction industry technician and craft level trades, electrical and electronics, machining, welding, refrigeration and air conditioning, plumbing, carpentry, scaffolding, shuttering and aluminium fabrication. Four thousand students are currently being trained here.</p>

<p class="setprojectup"><strong><em>Improved assessment techniques and international certification for the Hunar Foundation (Since 2010)</em></strong></p>

<p>The Hunar Foundation, which was established and supported by Pakistan&rsquo;s largest philanthropic fund, the Citizen Foundation, empowers youth and supports entrepreneurship through vocational training. SKILLS assisted the foundation to improve its assessment techniques and procedures. Approximately 1500 students are trained annually at two centres in programmes such as electrical installation, machining, refrigeration and air conditioning, plumbing and motor vehicle engineering.</p>

<p>Hunar Foundation has also recently started a separate programme to empower women by training them in the fields of &lsquo;hair and beauty&rsquo;, &lsquo;care givers&rsquo;, &lsquo;customer care&rsquo; and &lsquo;retailing&rsquo; so that they will be able to find employment and be financially secure.</p>

<p class="setprojectup"><strong><em>Empowering poor &amp; vulnerable youth from 4 impoverished districts of Punjab through technical &amp; vocational skills upgrading</em></strong></p>

<p>SKILLS lobbied with the sponsors of the Punjab Skills Development Fund (PSDF) to include City &amp; Guilds technical &amp; vocational qualification programmes to be recognized under its mandate to sponsor market driven training opportunities for poor and vulnerable populations of the 4 poorest districts of Punjab-Pakistan to improve their employability.</p>

<p>PSDF is a collaboration of the Punjab Government &amp; the Department for International Development (DFID) of UK. SKILLS&rsquo; facilitation has resulted in several private, public &amp; not-for-profit training institutions where City &amp; Guilds programmes have been implemented by SKILLS to receive funding from PSDF to train youth from Bahawalnagar, Bahawalpur, Lodhran &amp;Muzaffargarh &ndash; the 4 districts with the highest poverty headcount ratio in Punjab.</p>

<p>The success of the initial phase of the PSDF programme has encouraged the sponsors to extend the programme to 7 new districts this year, expanding further opportunities for providing impoverished youth with employable skills. &lsquo;SKILLS&rsquo; continues to play a vital hands-on role through advocacy, facilitation and implementation.</p>

<p class="setprojectup"><strong><em>Women&rsquo;s empowerment through vocational training (2012)</em></strong></p>

<p>Depilex is a well-known chain of training centres in Pakistan that provides training for disadvantaged women in hairdressing and beauty therapy as a means of livelihood. Several of the women are also burn-victims resulting from domestic violence and other types of abuse. This program offers them an opportunity to learn a new trade and provide for themselves. Depilex runs their highly sought-after programmes from 30 centres located across the country.</p>

<p>SKILLS provided training in Sri Lanka for Depilex in new techniques that were not available in Pakistan. Following this, several Depilex outlets upgraded to training centres where women can pursue professional courses in hairdressing and beauty therapy under City &amp; Guilds certification.</p>

<p class="setprojectup"><strong><em>SKILLS support to TVET institutions as a change facilitator</em></strong></p>

<p>&lsquo;SKILLS &lsquo;continues to facilitate iconic institutions - National Institute of Science &amp; Technical Education (NISTE); Technical Training Institute, Dharki(an Engro subsidiary);Institute Of Tourism &amp; Hotel Management (ITHM);Hashoo Foundation; Institute of Rural Management (Rawalpindi); Pakistan Knitwear Training Institute, Precision System Training Centre of the government, Trojans International, Coca Cola, the Trade Development Authority of Pakistan National Logistics Cell, Vocational Education Training Development Awareness Raising Organization - VETDACO (NTB), Mansol and TEVTA Sindh- in the areas of: implementing demand driven international vocational qualifications, TOT for faculty/management on curriculum implementation, assessment techniques, standardization of academic processes, teaching learning resources, promotional strategies, collaborating with donor agencies and sharing of international best practices.</p>

